PayType.description: Represents the type of pay provided to the field service worker that determines the hourly rate based on a labor agreement.

Payment.description: Represents a single event when a shopper makes a payment. For credit cards, this event is a payment capture or payment sale, but it doesn't appear on the shopper's credit card statement.
Payment.label: Payment

PaymentAuthAdjustment.description: Shows information about an adjustment made to an authorized transaction.
PaymentAuthAdjustment.label: Payment Authorization Adjustment

PaymentAuthorization.description: Represents a single payment authorization event where users can capture or reverse a payment against a reserve of funds.
PaymentAuthorization.label: Payment Authorization

PaymentBatchRun.description: Represents a batch processing job that processes payments in Billing. During a payment batch run, all the payment schedules that meet the specified criteria are processed and the corresponding Payment records are created. These payments are then applied to invoices or invoice lines.

PaymentCredit.description: Tracks the amount of money returned to the customer. The return can be a store credit, a gift card, or another type of credit. It's linked to the original payment record and includes the total credit amount issued.
PaymentCredit.label: Payment Credit

PaymentGateway.description: Platform object that represents the connection to an external payment gateway.
PaymentGateway.label: Payment Gateway

PaymentGatewayLog.description: Stores information exchanged between the Salesforce payments platform and external payment gateways. Gateway logs can also record payloads from external payment entities.
PaymentGatewayLog.label: Payment Gateway Log

PaymentGatewayProvider.description: Represents the payment gateway provider processing payments.
PaymentGatewayProvider.label: Payment Gateway Provider

PaymentGroup.description: Top-level object that groups all payment transactions that are processed for an order or invoice. PaymentGroup is a standalone object, so it isn’t required for users to execute payment transactions (authorizations, captures, refunds, and sales).
PaymentGroup.label: Payment Group

PaymentInitiationSource.description: Represents the originating source of a payment. This information helps other Salesforce products integrate with Salesforce Payments. This object is available in API version 63.0 and later.

PaymentIntent.description: Represents data temporarily stored during a transaction’s lifecycle that can identify the buyer, the merchant, and the amount the buyer is sending to the merchant. Data such as timestamp and amount returned can also be stored in PaymentIntent.

PaymentLineInvoice.description: Represents a payment allocated to or unallocated from an invoice.
PaymentLineInvoice.label: Payment Line Invoice

PaymentLineInvoiceLine.description: Represents information about a payment line that's applied to or unapplied from an invoice line.

PaymentLink.description: A link that a merchant can share with customers to collect payments for products and services. The payment link, which you can embed into a Salesforce app or send directly to a customer, directs the customer to a Pay Now payment page. The page can show a total amount owed or an itemized list or products, shipping and tax charges, and a total amount owed. The customer enters their contact and payment details, and submits their payment. The amounts are shown in the store's currency.

PaymentMandate.description: Represents information about the payment mandates given by a customer to their bank or financial institution to authorize a third party to collect payments from their account.
PaymentMandate.label: Payment Mandate

PaymentMethod.description: Represents the method that a buyer uses to compensate the seller of a good or service. Common payment methods include cash, checks, credit or debit cards, money orders, bank transfers, and online payment services.
PaymentMethod.label: Payment Method

PaymentRequest.description: Represents a financial compensation request for goods or services provided by a third party.
PaymentRequest.label: Payment Request

PaymentRequestLine.description: Represents the line item details of the financial compensation request.
PaymentRequestLine.label: Payment Request Line

PaymentSchedule.description: Represents information about a set of payments that a customer wants to collect at different times for a certain record. A schedule contains one or more payment schedule items, where each item represents one payment to be processed. Each of a schedule’s items can have different payment configuration fields, such as payment methods, payment dates, and payment accounts. When a payment scheduler launches a payment run, the run evaluates active payment schedule items, and picks them up for payment processing if they match the scheduler’s payment criteria.

PaymentScheduleItem.description: Represents information about a payment to be processed. Each schedule item can have different payment configuration fields, such as payment methods, payment dates, and payment accounts. When a payment scheduler launches a payment run, the run evaluates active payment schedule items, and picks them up for payment processing if they match the scheduler’s payment criteria.

PaymentSchedulePolicy.description: Represents information about the configuration for the payment schedule.

PaymentScheduleTreatment.description: Represents information about the processing of payment schedules including the payment method and the payment amount for the payment schedule.

PaymentScheduleTreatmentDtl.description: Represents information about the processing of payment schedules after the corresponding invoices are posted.

PaymentTerm.description: Represents an agreement between a buyer and a seller about when payment is due for an invoice.

PaymentTermItem.description: Represents configuration of a payment term.

PcmtEmssnFctrSet.description: Represents a collection of emission factors that are used to convert spent amounts in procurement data to carbon emissions in tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalent (tCO₂e).
PcmtEmssnFctrSet.label: Procurement Emissions Factor Set

PcmtEmssnFctrSetItem.description: Represents the individual emissions factors for scope 3 procurement analysis. Here, the environmentally extended input-output (EEIO) model outputs are used as the emission factors in units of tCO₂e per million spent (currency not specified).
PcmtEmssnFctrSetItem.label: Procurement Emissions Factor Set Item

PendingOrderSummary.description: Object representing a B2C Commerce order ingested via High Scale Orders before an OrderSummary is created for it. Optimized for online transaction processing (OLTP).
PendingOrderSummary.label: Pending Order Summary

PendingServiceRouting.description: Represents the routing details of a work item that’s waiting to be routed or assigned.
PendingServiceRouting.label: Pending Service Routing

PendingServiceRoutingInteractionInfo.description: Represents PendingServiceRouting interaction information that’s used when work is routed to an agent. For a screen pop, it specifies which records to open when work is routed to an agent from a specific channel.
PendingServiceRoutingInteractionInfo.label: Pending Service Routing Interaction Information

PercentileBsdCareFeeAgreement.description: Specifies the payment terms for contracts of Percentile Based Care Fee Agreement.
PercentileBsdCareFeeAgreement.label: Percentile Based Care Fee Agreement

Period.description: Represents a fiscal period defined in FiscalYearSettings.
Period.label: Period

Permission Update Event Type.description: Permission update events represent changes to object, field, and user permissions and setup entity access that occur in profiles and permission sets. The event type also tracks if you clone profiles or change whether session activation is required in permission sets or permission set groups.

PermissionDependency.description: Represents permission dependencies for a specified permission. For example, return all child dependencies for the Modify All Data permission.
PermissionDependency.label: Permission Dependency

PermissionSetAssignment.description: Represents a user’s assignment to a permission set or permission set group.
PermissionSetAssignment.label: Permission Set Assignment

PermissionSetGroupComponent.description: A junction object that relates the PermissionSetGroup and PermissionSet objects via their respective IDs; enables permission set group recalculation to determine the aggregated permissions for the group.
PermissionSetGroupComponent.label: Permission Set Group Component

PermissionSetLicense.description: Represents a license that’s used to enable one or more users to receive a specified permission without changing their profile or reassigning profiles. You can use permission set licenses to grant access, but not to deny access.
PermissionSetLicense.label: Permission Set License

PermissionSetLicenseAssign.description: Represents the association between a User and a PermissionSetLicense.
PermissionSetLicenseAssign.label: Permission Set License Assignment

PermissionSetLicenseDefinition (Develope.description: Represents the definition of a custom permission set license, which entitles specified features in a package.

PermissionUpdateEventLog.description: Permission update events represent changes to object, field, and user permissions and setup entity access that occur in profiles and permission sets. The event type also tracks if you clone profiles or change whether session activation is required in permission sets or permission set groups.

PersonAcademicCredential.description: Represents an Academic Credential that a person has earned.

PersonAccountOwnerPowerUser.description: Represents a user who can own more than 50,000 customer or partner portal accounts. Person account owner power users can own a large number of either customer or partner users. Their role can’t be changed and they must be at the root of the role hierarchy. Person account owner power user objects can't be created if deferred sharing is turned on for your org. Person account owner power user objects can be created while deferred sharing is turned off for an org. Deferred sharing can be turned back on after person account owner power user objects have been created.
PersonAccountOwnerPowerUser.label: Person Account Owner Power User

PersonAffinity.description: Represents the affinity of a person.

PersonCompetency.description: Represents the skills and competencies of a person.

PersonDisability.description: Represents information about a person's disability.
PersonDisability.label: Person Disability

PersonEducation.description: Represents information about professional education for a person in a party role.
PersonEducation.label: Person Education

PersonEmployment.description: Represents information about a person’s employment.
PersonEmployment.label: Person Employment

PersonExamination.description: Represents the examinations taken by a person.

PersonPublicProfile.description: Represents information about a user that’s shown on their public profile.

PersonPublicProfilePrefSet.description: Represents the user’s preferences for which data is included in their directory entry, as well as if they show up at all.

PersonTraining.description: Represents an assignment of a learning module in Workforce Engagement.

PersonTrait.description: Represents the traits of a person.

PersonalOrgInfo.description: Represents the information for a Tableau Next personal org.

PgmBasedHlthRskAdjFctr.description: Stores the risk adjustment factor for patients and members based on their eligibility for certain benefits programs. For instance, Medicaid in the US.
PgmBasedHlthRskAdjFctr.label: Program Based Risk Health Adjustment Factor

PickTicket.description: A PickTicket represents quantities of one or more products to be picked for fulfillment at a location. It can include products belonging to one or more fulfillment orders.
PickTicket.label: Pick Ticket

PickTicketAssignment.description: Represents the association of a FulfillmentOrder with a PickTicket. A PickTicket has one PickTicketAssignment for each FulfillmentOrder containing products to be picked as part of that PickTicket.
PickTicketAssignment.label: Pick Ticket Assignment

PickTicketProduct.description: Represents a quantity of a product to be picked as part of a PickTicket. It can include quantities for multiple FulfillmentOrders.
PickTicketProduct.label: Pick Ticket Product

PicklistValueInfo.description: Represents the active picklist values for a given picklist field.
PicklistValueInfo.label: Picklist Value Info

PipelineInspMetricConfig.description: Represents the configuration of a forecast category metric that appears in the Pipeline Inspection view.
PipelineInspMetricConfig.label: Pipeline Inspection Metric Configuration

PipelineInspMetricConfigLocalization.description: Represents the translated label of a Pipeline Inspection metric.
PipelineInspMetricConfigLocalization.label: Translation

PipelineInspectionListView.description: Represents a pipeline view, an intelligence view, or a saved filter. A pipeline view shows a set of opportunity records, based on specific criteria. An intelligence view shows a set of account, lead, or contact records, based on specific criteria.
PipelineInspectionListView.label: Pipeline Inspection List View

PipelineInspectionSumField.description: Use this object to learn which field from the opportunity object is used to aggregate Pipeline Inspection metrics on a pipeline view.
PipelineInspectionSumField.label: Pipeline Inspection Summary Field

PlanBenefit.description: Represents the standard benefits available under a plan that the purchaser offers to their members.
PlanBenefit.label: Plan Benefit

PlanBenefitItem.description: Represents the details of a benefit available under a purchaser’s plan that is offered to their members.
PlanBenefitItem.label: Plan Benefit Item

Platform Encryption Event Type.description: Platform Encryption event contains information about tenant secret and derived encryption key usage.

PlatformAction.description: PlatformAction is a virtual read-only object. It enables you to query for actions displayed in the UI, given a user, a context, device format, and a record ID. Examples include standard and custom buttons, quick actions, and productivity actions.
PlatformAction.label: Platform Action

PlatformEventSubscriberConfig.description: Represents configuration settings for a platform event Apex trigger, including the batch size and the trigger’s running user.
PlatformEventSubscriberConfig.label: Platform Event Subscriber Configuration

PlatformEventUsageMetric.description: Contains usage data for event publishing and delivery to CometD and Pub/Sub API clients, empApi Lightning components, and event relays. If Enhanced Usage Metrics isn't enabled, usage data is available for the last 24 hours, ending at the last hour, and for historical daily usage. In API 58.0 and later, you can enable Enhanced Usage Metrics to get usage data by event name and client for granular time intervals. PlatformEventUsageMetric contains separate usage metrics for platform events and change data capture events.
PlatformEventUsageMetric.label: Platform Event Usage Metric

PltnImpactRiskOppSummary.description: Represents the pollution impacts, risks, and opportunities that a company discloses as part of ESRS E3 - Water and marine resources.
PltnImpactRiskOppSummary.label: Pollution Impact Risk Opportunity Summary

Polygon.description: Represents a polygon with the polygon mapping data stored as a blob.

PortalDelegablePermissionSet.description: PortalDelegablePermissionSet is a base platform object used to store permission sets that can be assigned by a delegated portal/external user admin (DPUA) to portal users.
PortalDelegablePermissionSet.label: Portal Delegable Permission Set

Position.description: Represents a functional role that is characterized by specific duties and responsibilities, and required skills and qualifications.

PositionPayGrade.description: Represents a junction between a position and a pay grade.

PositionQualification.description: Represents a position-based qualification. For example, Communication Skills for a Program and Management Analyst position.

PresenceConfigDeclineReason.description: Represents the settings for a decline reason that a presence user provides when declining work.
PresenceConfigDeclineReason.label: Presence Configuration Decline Reason

PresenceUserConfigProfile.description: Represents a configuration that determines the settings that are assigned to presence users who are assigned to a specific profile. User-level configurations override profile-level configurations.
PresenceUserConfigProfile.label: Presence Configuration for Profile

PresenceUserConfigUser.description: Represents a configuration that determines the settings that are assigned to a presence user. These user-level configurations override profile-level configurations.
PresenceUserConfigUser.label: Presence Configuration for User

PreventiveCareAgreement.description: Specifies the payment terms for contracts of Preventive Care Fee Agreement.
PreventiveCareAgreement.label: Preventive Care Agreement

PriceAdjustmentGroupShape.description: Defines the business logic for a top-level price adjustment, for example, a discount applied to an entire order.

PriceAdjustmentItemShape.description: Defines the business logic for an item-level price adjustment, for example, a discount on an order item.

PriceAdjustmentSchedule.description: Represents a series of tiered discounts based on the number of items purchased.

PriceAdjustmentTier.description: Represents a discount tier in a price adjustment schedule.

PriceBook2.description: Represents a price book that contains the list of products that your org sells.

PriceBookEntry.description: Represents a product entry (an association between a Pricebook2 and Product2) in a price book.

PriceBookEntryDerivedPrice.description: Represents the price of a product that’s derived from another source such as a product or an asset.

PriceBookRateCard.description: Represents a junction between price book and rate card objects.

PriceProtectExecLineItem.description: Represents a line item created as part of a Price Protection Execution.

PriceProtectionExecution.description: Represents an instance of running the price protection process, capturing execution time, status, and the effective date of price changes.

PriceProtectionTerm.description: Represents a configuration record that defines the rules, types, and eligible conditions for price protection.

PriceRevisionPolicy.description: Represents the guidelines and methods used to modify product or service prices, often incorporating formulas based on price revision entries and various adjustments. For example, a policy might dictate that prices are revised based on a formula that considers the regional Consumer Price Index (CPI) with a specific adjustment percentage, effective from a defined date, and categorized as either a flat adjustment or one directly based on the price revision entry data.

Pricebook2.description: Represents a price book that contains the list of products that your org sells.
Pricebook2.label: Price Book

PricebookEntry.description: Represents a product entry (an association between a Pricebook2 and Product2) in a price book.
PricebookEntry.label: Price Book Entry

PricebookEntryAdjustment.description: Read-only junction object created when you associate a price adjustment schedule with a price book entry.
PricebookEntryAdjustment.label: Price Book Entry Adjustment

Pricebookentry.description: Represents a product entry (an association between a price book and product) in a price book.

PricingAPIExecution.description: Represents the pricing resolution for an pricing element determined using strategy name and formula.

PricingActionParameters.description: Represents a pricing action associated to a context definition and a pricing procedure.

PricingAdjBatchJob.description: Represents the collective update of multiple records on their prices and other adjustments.

PricingAdjBatchJobLog.description: Represents the report that contains a list of failed adjustment requests along with an error message that describes the reason for failure.

PricingProcedureOutputMap.description: Represents the mapping of the outputs of the pricing procedures to the associated lookup tables. Each record specifies the output mapping of the associated lookup table based on the pricing component type specified in the Pricing Recipe Table Mapping object.

PricingProcedureResolution.description: Represents a selection for a pricing procedure to execute a pricing process from a list of pricing procedures available.

PricingProcessExecution.description: Represents a record generated during the execution of a discovery or pricing procedure. Multiple procedures may be performed within a single API call, with each recorded in a Pricing API Execution record.

PricingRecipe.description: Represents one out of various data models or sets of entities of a particular cloud that'll be consumed by the pricing data store during design and run time.

PricingRecipeTableMapping.description: Represents the mapping of pricing components of a lookup table with the chosen pricing recipe.

PrivacyHold.description: Represents a Privacy Hold that indicates that a record should be preserved from masking or deletion by Data Management policies in Privacy Center.
PrivacyHold.label: Privacy Hold

PrivacyHoldReason.description: Represents the business or legal purpose for why a record has a Privacy Hold.
PrivacyHoldReason.label: Privacy Hold Reason

PrivacyJobSession.description: Represents the status of past, ongoing, and scheduled policy jobs in Privacy Center.
PrivacyJobSession.label: Privacy Job Session

PrivacyObjectSession.description: Represents the status of each object being processed in past, ongoing, and scheduled policy jobs in Privacy Center.
PrivacyObjectSession.label: Privacy Object Session

PrivacyRTBFRequest.description: Represents a Right to Be Forgotten Request made in Privacy Center.
PrivacyRTBFRequest.label: Privacy RTBF Request

PrivacyRequest.description: See details and monitor the status of Data Subject Access Requests made in Privacy Center.
PrivacyRequest.label: Privacy Request

PrivacySessionRecordFailure.description: Represents error messages encountered during policy job executions in Privacy Center.
PrivacySessionRecordFailure.label: Privacy Session Record Failure

Problem.description: Problems represent the root cause data of one or more incidents. This object contains all the details of a problem, documenting the history of the problem from detection to closure.
Problem.label: Problem

ProblemDefinition.description: The definition of a care plan problem in the reusable PGI library that’s a part of Integrated Care Management. When instantiated, ProblemDefinition records create HealthCondition records that serve as problems in care plans.
ProblemDefinition.label: Problem Definition

ProblemGoalDefinition.description: A junction object that associated a goal definition to its parent problem definition. These junction records assist in establishing the problem-goal hierarchy in care plans instantiated from the PGI library.
ProblemGoalDefinition.label: Problem Goal Definition

ProblemIncident.description: Represents a junction object that relates a Problem to an Incident.
ProblemIncident.label: Related Problem and Incident

ProblemRelatedItem.description: Represents a junction object that relates a Problem to an Asset.
ProblemRelatedItem.label: Problem Related Item

ProcedureOutputResolution.description: Represents the pricing resolution for an pricing element determined using strategy name and formula.

ProcedurePlanCriterion.description: Represents a criterion within a procedure plan option record.

ProcedurePlanDefinition.description: Represents the setup of a unified procedure from a list of multiple procedures that can be sequenced in any order based on business needs. Each procedure plan definition contains sections and subsections where procedures can be configured by using a lookup table or rule-based criteria.

ProcedurePlanDefinitionVersion.description: Represents the versions for a procedure plan definition. Multiple versions under a procedure plan definition must be active at a time, which can be resolved at run time using the rank field.

ProcedurePlanOption.description: Represents the selection criteria of how a procedure can be configured for a selected procedure plan section record.

ProcedurePlanSection.description: Represents various procedure setup sections for a procedure plan definition. Each section enables the setup of a procedure of a type that can be further determined by using a rule-based criteria or it can be set based on a selected lookup table.

ProcedurePlanVariable.description: Represents the setup for any adhoc user-defined variable that can be linked to a procedure plan definition record.

ProcessDefinition.description: Represents the definition of a single approval process.
ProcessDefinition.label: Process Definition

ProcessException.description: Represents a business exception, such as a processing failure on an order summary. A separate process is required to resolve the failure that caused the process exception before processing can continue.
ProcessException.label: Process Exception

ProcessFlowMigration.description: Represents a process's migrated criteria and the resulting migrated flow.
ProcessFlowMigration.label: Process Flow Migration

ProcessInstance.description: Represents an instance of a single, end-to-end approval process. Use this and the node, step, and workitem process instance objects to create approval history reports.
ProcessInstance.label: Process Instance

ProcessInstanceNode.description: Represents a step in an instance of an approval process. Compare to ProcessNode, which describes the step in a process definition. Use this object to retrieve approval history.
ProcessInstanceNode.label: Process Instance Node

ProcessInstanceStep.description: Represents one work item in an approval process (ProcessInstance).
ProcessInstanceStep.label: Process Instance Step

ProcessInstanceWorkitem.description: Represents a user’s pending approval request.
ProcessInstanceWorkitem.label: Approval Request

ProcessNode.description: Describes a step in a process definition. Compare to ProcessInstanceNode, which describes a step in a running process.
ProcessNode.label: Process Node

ProdtAttrMappedScope.description: Represents a junction between the product attribute scope and the product classification attribute.
ProdtAttrMappedScope.label: Product Attribute Mapped Scope

ProdtAttrScope.description: Represents the scope definition for a product attribute so that it can be used during claims processing.
ProdtAttrScope.label: Product Attribute Scope

ProdtDecompEnrchVarMap.description: Represents the mapping of a field context tag or an attribute to a variable within an expression set.

Producer.description: Represents an agent or an agency selling insurance.
Producer.label: Producer

ProducerCommission.description: Represents a producer's commission for an insurance policy. The commission can be calculated from the commissionable transactions or can be populated from an external system.
ProducerCommission.label: Producer Commission

ProducerPolicyAssignment.description: A junction object that associates the Insurance Policy object with the Producer object. This object represents the producers who are managing the same insurance policy.

Product2.description: Represents a product that your company sells. Custom fields extend the standard Product object for use in Consumer Goods Cloud.
Product2.label: Product

Product2DataTranslation.description: Represents the translated values of the data stored within a Product2 record’s fields.
Product2DataTranslation.label: Product Translation

ProductAttribute.description: Represents the attributes that can be associated with a product.
ProductAttribute.label: Product Attribute

ProductAttributeDefinition.description: Represents the relationship between a product and its attributes.

ProductAttributeSet.description: Used to group variation attributes that apply to one or more products.
ProductAttributeSet.label: Product Attribute Set

ProductAttributeSetItem.description: Represents a set of attributes that can be associated with a product.
ProductAttributeSetItem.label: Product Attribute Set Item

ProductAttributeSetProduct.description: Represents the product associated with a set of attributes.
ProductAttributeSetProduct.label: Product Attribute Set Product

ProductAvailabilityProjection.description: Represents the projected product quantity available at an inventory location at various points in time. Records for this object are automatically created by Intelligent Sales.
ProductAvailabilityProjection.label: Product Availability Projection

ProductCatalog.description: The container that holds a Product Category hierarchy.
ProductCatalog.label: Catalog

ProductCategory.description: Represents the category that products are organized in.
ProductCategory.label: Category

ProductCategoryDataTranslation.description: Represents the translated values for the data stored within a ProductCategory record’s fields.
ProductCategoryDataTranslation.label: Category Translation

ProductCategoryDisqual.description: Represents disqualification rules for product categories. The rules determine when the product category doesn’t qualify to be displayed to users.

ProductCategoryProduct.description: Holds the relation between product and product category to assign products to a category.
ProductCategoryProduct.label: Product Category Product

ProductCategoryQualification.description: Represents qualification rules for product categories. The rules determine when the product category qualifies to be displayed to users.

ProductClassification.description: Represents a template that holds a collection of dynamic attributes. Product classification is used to quickly define and create multiple products that are similar yet different.

ProductClassificationAttr.description: Represents the relationship between a product classification and its attributes. This is the default configuration for products based on the product classification.

ProductComponentGroup.description: Represents the logical grouping of associated products in a bundle and the products’ arrangement policy (group cardinality).
ProductComponentGroup.label: Product Component Group

ProductComponentGrpOverride.description: Represents override information for a Product Component Group. The cardinality of the product component group can be overridden in the context of a product bundle.

ProductConfigFlowAssignment.description: A junction object that represents the many-to-many relationship between Product Configuration Flow, Product, and Product Classification.

ProductConfigurationFlow.description: Specifies the many-to-many relationship between Product Classification, Product, and Flow Definition objects. The flow definition is used to configure standalone and bundled products of a specific product classification along with the product attributes, quantities, and product selling models.

ProductConfigurationRule.description: Represents the validation, inclusion, and exclusion rules for products in the context of the selling process. The selling process can be quoting, configuration, or ordering.

ProductConsumed.description: Represents an item from your product inventory that was used to complete a work order or work order line item.
ProductConsumed.label: Product Consumed

ProductConsumedState.description: Represents an action taken to associate a serialized product with a product transfer. The new state is a result of the action. A product transfer state record is created when serialized products are attached to the product transfer.
ProductConsumedState.label: Product Consumed State

ProductCoverage.description: A junction object that associates the Product object with the CoverageType object. You see this object only if you have enabled the Access Master List of Coverage Types org pref.

ProductDecompEnrichmentRule.description: Represents mappings between fields and attributes. Enrichment rules are part of a decomposition rule, and are used to propagate data to fulfillment order lines.

ProductDetectedPriceChange.description: Represents a detected change in price for a product associated with a partner account.

ProductDisqualification.description: Represents disqualification rules for products. The rules determine when the product doesn’t qualify to be displayed to users. The rules are based on user context.

ProductEmissionsFactor.description: Represents information about the emissions factors used in quantifying the emissions by a product in the supply-chain.
ProductEmissionsFactor.label: Product Emissions Factor

ProductEntitlementTemplate.description: Represents predefined terms of customer support (Entitlement) that users can add to products (Product2).
ProductEntitlementTemplate.label: Product Entitlement Template

ProductFaultCode.description: Represents a relationship between a product or product family and the fault code.
ProductFaultCode.label: Product Fault Code

ProductFeaturedProduct.description: Represents the user-defined collection of featured products that are meant to cross-sell or upsell with your product.
ProductFeaturedProduct.label: Product Featured Product

ProductFee.description: Represents the base fee associated with a product.

ProductFulfillmentDecompRule.description: Represents a rule that determines how an order is broken into sub-orders with specific technical details that help in order fulfillment. It can be applied to a commercial or a technical product.

ProductFulfillmentLocation.description: Associates a business account and a product inventory with the responsible field rep.
ProductFulfillmentLocation.label: Product Fulfillment Location

ProductFulfillmentScenario.description: Represents a link between a product and the corresponding group of fulfillment steps that's necessary to fulfill that product.

ProductInvSearchableField.description: Represents a dataset on inventory information that's the basis for searching product inventory. Contains multiple fields from Product Item and related objects.

ProductInventoryBatchSearchableField.description: Represents production batch data used for inventory search, including batch item details for a specific location. This data serves as the basis for Criteria-Based and Filter Search, which combines batch details with standard inventory dimensions.

ProductItem.description: Represents the stock of a product at a particular inventory location, such as a warehouse or a distribution lot. Product item records represent your inventory. A product item is associated with an inventory location and stores the quantity of products at that location.
ProductItem.label: Product Item

ProductItemTransaction.description: Represents an action taken on a product item. Product item transactions track when a product is consumed, replenished, adjusted, or transferred. Product item transactions are auto-generated records that specify the quantity of products impacted by the action.
ProductItemTransaction.label: Product Item Transaction

ProductLaborCode.description: Represents a junction between the labor code that's applicable to a product or product family and the required standard effort.
ProductLaborCode.label: Product Labor Code

ProductListRate.description: Represents the list rate of the product.

ProductMedia.description: Represents the rich media, including images and attachments, that can be added to products.
ProductMedia.label: Product Media

ProductPriceHistoryLog.description: Stores historical pricing data based on the product's price range.

ProductPriceRange.description: Represents the price range of a product determined by using a product selling model that’s stored in the relevant price book.

ProductQualification.description: Represents qualification rules for products. The rules determine when the product qualifies to be displayed to users. The rules are based on user context.

ProductQuantityRule.description: Represents the relationship between a quantity rule and a product. This object assigns quantity rules to a product.
ProductQuantityRule.label: Product Quantity Rule

ProductRampSegment.description: Represents the ramp period within a ramp deal where terms, volumes, and other commitments change over time.

ProductRelComponentOverride.description: Represents the cardinality overrides for product components in a bundle.

ProductRelatedComponent.description: Represents a product that is included in a product bundle, a set, or a product and an add-on.
ProductRelatedComponent.label: Product Related Component

ProductRelatedMaterial.description: Represents information about the components of a product.
ProductRelatedMaterial.label: Product Related Material

ProductRelationshipType.description: Defines the relationship between two sales transaction items. For example, defines a relationship between a bundle and a bundle component.
ProductRelationshipType.label: Product Relationship Type

ProductRequest.description: Represents a request or an order for products to and from specific inventory locations.
ProductRequest.label: Product Request

ProductRequestLineItem.description: Represents a product that’s requested as a part of a product request. Product request line items are components of product requests. Each line item is associated with a specific product being requested.
ProductRequestLineItem.label: Product Request Line Item

ProductRequired.description: Represents a product that is needed to complete a work order or work order line item.
ProductRequired.label: Product Required

ProductSellingModel.description: Defines one method by which a product can be sold; for example, as a one-time sale, an evergreen subscription, or a termed subscription. If the product is sold on subscription, this object defines the subscription’s term. A product can have multiple product selling models.

ProductSellingModelDataTranslation.description: Represents the translated values of the data stored within the ProductSellingModel record’s fields.

ProductSellingModelOption.description: A junction object between Product Selling Model and Product2.

ProductServiceCampaign.description: Represents a set of activities to be performed for a product service campaign. For example, a recall of products due to potential safety hazards or an upgrade of products to comply with legal regulations.
ProductServiceCampaign.label: Product Service Campaign

ProductServiceCampaignItem.description: Represents an item, such as an asset or a serialized product, that’s included in a product service campaign.
ProductServiceCampaignItem.label: Product Service Campaign Item

ProductServiceCampaignItemStatus.description: Represents a status for a product service campaign item in field service.
ProductServiceCampaignItemStatus.label: Product Service Campaign Item Status

ProductServiceCampaignStatus.description: Represents a status for a product service campaign in field service.
ProductServiceCampaignStatus.label: Product Service Campaign Status

ProductSpecificationRecType.description: Represents the association of a product specification type with record types defined on the Product object. The product specification record type also determines if the product specification is sold commercially or not.

ProductSpecificationType.description: Represents the specification types in your org that define products with unique terminology specific to the industry.

ProductSurcharge.description: Represents an association between a product and a surcharge.
ProductSurcharge.label: Product Surcharge

ProductTransfer.description: Represents the transfer or the movement of a product item between two inventory locations.
ProductTransfer.label: Product Transfer

ProductTransferState.description: Represents an action taken to associate a serialized product with a product transfer. The new state is a result of the action. A product transfer state record is created when serialized products are attached to the product transfer.
ProductTransferState.label: Product Transfer State

ProductUsageGrant.description: Represents the details of a grant associated with a resource, product, or service, such as the purchased quantity, renewal and rollover policy, and validity of the grant.

ProductUsageResource.description: Represents the mapping of a product and its usage resources.

ProductUsageResourcePolicy.description: Represents the policies applicable to the usage resource when it’s associated with a sellable product. These policies are derived from the parent usage resource and can be overridden when setting up usage modeling.

ProductWarrantyTerm.description: Defines the relationship between a product or product family and a warranty term.
ProductWarrantyTerm.label: Product Warranty Term

ProfileSkill.description: Represents a profile skill, which describes a user’s professional knowledge. This is a global record for the organization, and users are associated through the ProfileSkillUser object.
ProfileSkill.label: Skill

ProfileSkillEndorsement.description: Represents a detail relationship of ProfileSkillUser. An endorsement of a profile skill shows approval and support of another user’s publicly declared skill.
ProfileSkillEndorsement.label: Endorsement

ProfileSkillUser.description: Represents a detail relationship of User. The object connects profile skills with users.
ProfileSkillUser.label: Skill User

Program.description: Represents information about the enrollment and disbursement of benefits in a program.

ProgramApplnFormTemplate.description: Represents an application form template used to enroll in a program.

ProgramEnrlEligibilityCrit.description: Represents a junction between Program and Enrollment Eligibility Criteria objects.

ProgramEnrollment.description: Represents details of enrollment for benefits in a program.

ProgramInitiative.description: Represents information about a sustainability initiative in a program.

ProgramInitiativeEnrl.description: Represents the enrollment details of a sustainability initiative in a program.

ProgramRebateType.description: Represents a rebate structure associated with a Rebate Program.

ProgramRecommendationRule.description: Represents the eligibility criteria and recommendation for a program.

ProgramTermApplnTimeline.description: Represents a junction between Academic Term, Application Timeline, and Learning Program objects.

Promotion.description: Create promotional activities that are either part of a campaign or isolated targeted promotions to run at retail stores.
Promotion.label: Promotion

PromotionActionableList.description: Represent of a junction between a promotion and an actionable list.
PromotionActionableList.label: Promotion Actionable List

PromotionChannel.description: Associate a promotion with a store, store group, or an account.

PromotionExecEvalGrpItem.description: Represents either a promotion or a promotion group in a promotion execution evaluation group.

PromotionLimit.description: Represents the limit of a promotion.

PromotionLimitUsage.description: Represents information about the total usage of a promotion limit.

PromotionLineItemRule.description: Lists compound conditions about a promotion.
PromotionLineItemRule.label: Promotion Line Item Rule

PromotionLoyaltyPtnrProdt.description: Represents a relationship between a promotion and a loyalty partner product. It indicates the products or product categories that are applied to a particular promotion.
PromotionLoyaltyPtnrProdt.label: Promotion Loyalty Partner Product

PromotionMarketSegment.description: Represents a relationship between a promotion and Data Cloud segment. It indicates the segments targeted for a particular promotion.
PromotionMarketSegment.label: Promotion Market Segment

PromotionPartyUsage.description: Represents the details of number of times a promotion has been used by a customer.
PromotionPartyUsage.label: Promotion Party Usage

PromotionPartyUsageDetail.description: Represents the amount that's discounted by a promotion for a transaction journal.

PromotionProduct.description: Associate a promotion with a product.

PromotionProductCategory.description: Associate a promotional activity with a product category.

PromotionQualifier.description: Represents the product, product category, or order that you want to target with your promotion qualifier in a B2B or D2C store.
PromotionQualifier.label: Promotion Qualifier

PromotionRuleTemplate.description: Represents the configuration of a promotion rule template.
PromotionRuleTemplate.label: Promotion Rule Template

PromotionSegment.description: Represents a promotion segment, which you can assign to different stores or buyer groups, allowing them to access the promotion.
PromotionSegment.label: Promotion Segment

PromotionSegmentBuyerGroup.description: Represents a promotion segment, associated with a buyer group, and used for B2B Commerce.
PromotionSegmentBuyerGroup.label: Promotion Segment Buyer Group

PromotionSegmentSalesStore.description: Represents a promotion segment, associated with a store, and used for B2B Commerce.
PromotionSegmentSalesStore.label: Promotion Segment Sales Store

PromotionStage.description: Represents a stage when the promotion sends an email to the promotion's target audience. With Global Promotions Management, a promotion launch email is sent after the promotion is activated.
PromotionStage.label: Promotion Stage

PromotionStageEmailTemplate.description: Represents a junction between a promotion stage and an email template. With Global Promotions Management, a promotion's launch email is associated with the promotion's Promotion Launched stage. You can customize the promotion launch email based on your company’s branding.
PromotionStageEmailTemplate.label: Promotion Stage Email Template

PromotionTarget.description: Represents the product, product category, or order that you want to target with your promotion in a B2B Store or D2C store.
PromotionTarget.label: Promotion Target

PromotionTier.description: Represents a tier of a promotion that includes multiple tiers. A promotion can have up to 10 tiers.
PromotionTier.label: Promotion Tier

PromptAction.description: Represents how the user interacted with the in-app guidance prompt or walkthrough.
PromptAction.label: Prompt Action

PromptActionOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents a rule which determines PromptAction sharing access for the owners.
PromptActionOwnerSharingRule.label: Prompt Action Owner Rule

PromptError.description: Represents the error or warning associated with the PromptAction.
PromptError.label: Prompt Error

PromptLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of a label for record details about in-app guidance when the Translation Workbench is enabled for your org.
PromptLocalization.label: Translation

PromptVersionLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of a label for-app guidance when the Translation Workbench is enabled for your org.
PromptVersionLocalization.label: Translation

ProrationPolicy.description: Defines how the price of a subscription is divided into time periods and how the price is calculated for each time period.
ProrationPolicy.label: Proration Policy

ProviderNetworkContract.description: Represents a provider and a network bound together by a contract.
ProviderNetworkContract.label: Provider Network Contract

ProviderNetworkTier.description: Represents unique tiers for each provider network.
ProviderNetworkTier.label: Provider Network Tier

ProviderOffering.description: Represents people or organizations associated with providing benefits to program participants.

ProviderSearchSyncLog.description: Represents a log with information about the provider search data sync status of a healthcare provider record.
ProviderSearchSyncLog.label: Provider Search Sync Log

PublicComplaint.description: Represents the complaints submitted by public users. This object is available in API version 49.0 and later.
PublicComplaint.label: Public Complaint

PulseCheck.description: Represents the wellbeing of a learner based on a primary metric or criteria at a specific date and time.

PulseCheckTemplate.description: Represents a common template used to create Pulse Check records.

PurchaseQuantityRule.description: Represents a rule that restricts the quantity of a product that can be purchased. The rule can be an increment, minimum, or maximum rule.
PurchaseQuantityRule.label: Quantity Rule

PurchaserPlan.description: Represents the payer plan that a purchaser makes available to its members and members’ dependents.
PurchaserPlan.label: Purchaser Plan

PurchaserPlanAssn.description: Represents a junction object that associates the purchaser to the plans they offer to members.
PurchaserPlanAssn.label: Purchaser Plan Association

PushTopic.description: Represents a query that is the basis for notifying Streaming API clients of changes to records in an org.
PushTopic.label: Push Topic

PymtSchdDistributionMethod.description: Represents information about the partial payments that the total payment is divided into.

Question.description: Represents a question in a zone that users can view and reply to.

QuestionDataCategorySelection.description: A data category selection represents a data category that classifies a question.

QuestionReportAbuse.description: Represents a user-reported abuse on a Question in a Chatter Answers zone.

QuestionSubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following a Question.

Queued Execution Event Type.description: Queued Execution events contain details about queued executions—for example, batch Apex.

QueuedExecutionEventLog.description: Queued Execution events contain details about queued executions—for example, batch Apex.

QuickActionDefinition.description: Represents the definition of a quick action.
QuickActionDefinition.label: Action

QuickText.description: This object stores a snippet of text that allows users to send a quick response to a customer. Use quick text to create greetings, answers to common questions, short notes, and more.
QuickText.label: Quick Text

QuickTextUsage.description: Represents the usage of quick text on a record, including which quick text was used, who used it, and how they used it.
QuickTextUsage.label: Quick Text Usage

QuotLineItmUsageRsrcPlcy.description: Represents the policies that are used for the usage resource that's associated with the usage product added in the quote line item.

QuotLineItmUseRsrcGrant.description: Represents the negotiated grants for the usage resource that's associated with the usage product added in the quote line item.

Quote.description: Represents a quote, which is a record showing proposed prices for products and services.
Quote.label: Quote

QuoteAction.description: Indicates the type of sales transaction that’s being quoted; for example, a renewal sale.

QuoteAdjustmentGroup.description: Group containing a set of adjustments applied to a quote.

QuoteDocument.description: Represents a quote in document format.
QuoteDocument.label: Quote PDF

QuoteItemTaxItem.description: The tax that is applied to a quote line item.
QuoteItemTaxItem.label: Quote Item Tax Item

QuoteLineDetail.description: Represents the breakdown details of a quote line item. Revenue Cloud generates these records to capture pricing and quantity changes, such as negative quantity reductions, early renewals, derived pricing or repricing during an amendment, and bundle or product attribute reconfigurations.

QuoteLineGroup.description: Stores the group information for line items in a quote. It also stores the aggregated line field information (subtotal). It contains a parent-child relationship to quote.

QuoteLineItem.description: Represents a quote line item, which is a member of the list of Product2 products associated with a Quote, along with other information about those line items on that quote.
QuoteLineItem.label: Quote Line Item

QuoteLineItemAttribute.description: Represents a virtual object that stores an attribute specified for a quote line item.

QuoteLineItemGroupClass.description: Represents the association of a Quote Line Item to GroupClass. Use this entity for large group quoting process when multiple group classes are attributed on a single quote line item. Child object of Quote.
QuoteLineItemGroupClass.label: Quote Line Item Group Class

QuoteLineItemRecipient.description: Represents a site, employee, or other entity for which services are being quoted. This could include details such as the recipient's name, contact information, associated site or location, and any specific requirements or preferences for the quoted services.
QuoteLineItemRecipient.label: Quote Line Item Recipient

QuoteLineItemRelatedObject.description: Represents the junction between a Quote Line Item and a related object. The values of the attributes from the related object are referenced by the relevant product attributes on the Quote LIne Item
QuoteLineItemRelatedObject.label: Quote Line Item Related Object

QuoteLinePriceAdjustment.description: Indicates the calculated price adjustment that is applied to the quote line, for example, a calculated volume discount or the prorated value of a manual discount. Use the quote line price adjustment to inform potential customers about the type, value, and total amount of their discounts.
QuoteLinePriceAdjustment.label: Quote Line Price Adjustment

QuoteLineRateAdjustment.description: Represents the negotiated rate adjustment for a quote line item.

QuoteLineRateCardEntry.description: Represents the catalog and negotiated rates of a usage resource associated with a quote line item that's used to charge overage consumption.

QuoteLineRelationship.description: Describes the relationship between quote line items, such as items in a bundle.
QuoteLineRelationship.label: Quote Line Relationship

QuoteLineWorkSource.description: Represents an association between a quote and work sources, such as assets, quote line items, order products, or work type groups.
QuoteLineWorkSource.label: Quote Line Work Source

QuoteRecipientGroup.description: Represents a recipient group for which offers or products with the same configuration are being added. This also includes reusing these groups to add or remove recipients.
QuoteRecipientGroup.label: Quote Recipient Group

QuoteRecipientGroupMember.description: Represents a junction between a quote line item recipient and a quote recipient group.
QuoteRecipientGroupMember.label: Quote Recipient Group Member

REST API Event Type.description: REST API events contain details about REST-specific requests.

RateAdjustmentByAttribute.description: Represents the adjustments that determine the rate of a resource based on its rate-impacting attributes. These attributes are linked to the usage product record. Rates are then influenced by conditions specified in the Attribute Based Adjustment Condition object. Finally, the charge rate is determined by using the Attribute Based Adjustment Rule object.

RateAdjustmentByTier.description: Represents the adjustments for the rate of a resource that’s determined based on the specified tiers. This object stores information about the type of adjustment used, the value of the adjustment type, and any applicable boundaries.

RateCard.description: Represents the rules used to rate the consumption of a group of resources within a product. Usage of a resource is billed at a specified rate if the user consumes more than their allowance for a time period.

RateCardEntry.description: Represents a rule that determines the charge rate for using a product's resource. Each entry is linked to one rate card exclusively, and its activation or deactivation can be controlled by assigning effective dates.

RatingFrequencyPolicy.description: Represents the policy that defines the frequency at which rating is triggered for the ratable summary records.

RatingRequest.description: Represents the common run-time parameters, such as context definition and rating procedure for a set of records in the rateable summary table.

RatingRequestBatchJob.description: Represents a junction between the rating request and batch job objects.

RebateClaim.description: Represents proof of sale of a vehicle submitted by a dealer in the form of a retail delivery report. This report can also be used for rebate payout calculations.

RecAlrtDataSrcExpSetDef.description: Represents information about the data source for a record alert and the association with an expression set definition.
RecAlrtDataSrcExpSetDef.label: Record Alert Data Source Expression Set Definition

ReceivedDocument.description: Contains a request for an operation to be performed on a document, such as rotating, splitting, or text extraction.
ReceivedDocument.label: Received Document

ReceivedDocumentType.description: Represents a junction object between Received Document and Document Type.
ReceivedDocumentType.label: Received Document Type

RecentFieldChange.description: Use this virtual object to see how an opportunity has changed in the past seven days. Learn the previous value of a field, who made the change, and when the change was made.
RecentFieldChange.label: Recent Field Change

RecentlyViewed.description: Represents metadata entities typically found in Setup such as page layout definitions, workflow rule definitions, and email templates that the current user has recently viewed.
RecentlyViewed.label: Recently Viewed

Recommendation.description: Represents the recommendations surfaced as offers and actions for Einstein Next Best Action.
Recommendation.label: Recommendation

RecommendationResponse.description: Represents the user responses to a presented offer or recommendation for Einstein Next Best Action. This object is available in API version 51.0 and later.
RecommendationResponse.label: Recommendation Response

RecordAction.description: Represents a relationship between a record and an action, such as a flow. Create a RecordAction for every action that you want to associate with a particular record.
RecordAction.label: RecordAction

RecordAggregationDefinition.description: Represents a data aggregation from one object to another object to which it is connected by other objects in the data model.
RecordAggregationDefinition.label: Record Aggregation Definition

RecordAggregationJoinCondition.description: Represents a condition in a join between two record aggregation objects.
RecordAggregationJoinCondition.label: Record Aggregation Join Condition

RecordAggregationObject.description: Represents an object in the record aggegation join sequence.
RecordAggregationObject.label: Record Aggregation Object

RecordAggregationObjectFilter.description: Represents a filter that is applied to the records of an object in the record aggregation join sequence.
RecordAggregationObjectFilter.label: Record Aggregation Object Filter

RecordAggregationResult.description: Represents a data aggregation from one record to another record based on the record aggregation definition for the corresponding objects.
RecordAggregationResult.label: Record Aggregation Result

RecordAlert.description: Represents an alert message about a specific record and tracks the status and active period of the alert.
RecordAlert.label: Record Alert

RecordAlertActionableTarget.description: Represents the action associated with the parent record alert.
RecordAlertActionableTarget.label: Record Alert Actionable Target

RecordAlertCategory.description: Represents a category to group and present record alerts.
RecordAlertCategory.label: Record Alert Category

RecordAlertCategoryLocalization.description: Represents the translated label of a RecordAlertCategory metadata type.
RecordAlertCategoryLocalization.label: Translation

RecordAlertDataSource.description: Represents an internal or external source for record alert data.
RecordAlertDataSource.label: Record Alert Data Source

RecordAlertDataTranslation.description: Represents the translated values of the data stored within a RecordAlert record’s fields.
RecordAlertDataTranslation.label: Record Alert Translation

RecordAlertTemplate.description: A template that is shown in the Alerts FlexCard when the expression set requirements are met.
RecordAlertTemplate.label: Record Alert Template

RecordTypeLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of a label for a record type when the Translation Workbench is enabled for your organization.
RecordTypeLocalization.label: Translation

RecordVisibility (Pilot).description: Represents the visibility attributes that determine a record’s read access.

RecordsetFilterCriteria.description: Represents a set of filters that can be used to match service appointments or assets based on your criteria fields.
RecordsetFilterCriteria.label: Recordset Filter Criteria

RecordsetFilterCriteriaRule.description: Represents a rule using fields from the designated source object to create filters on the filtered, or target, object.
RecordsetFilterCriteriaRule.label: Recordset Filter Criteria Rule

RecordsetFltrCritMonitor.description: Monitors whether the value of an asset attribute is within the threshold of a recordset filter criteria (RFC).
RecordsetFltrCritMonitor.label: Recordset Filter Criteria Monitor

RecruitmentContentSection.description: Represents the content that you want to include in a section of a recruitment posting.

RecruitmentPostingCntntSect.description: Represents a junction between a recruitment posting and a recruitment content section.

RecruitmentRequisition.description: Represents a formal request to recruit for a position or a provider vacancy.

RecruitmentRequisitionLoc.description: Represents a junction between recruitment requisition and location

RecruitmentRequisitionPtcp.description: Represents information about a user or group of participants who have access to a recruitment requisition.

RecurrenceSchedule.description: Represents the recurrence schedule for a benefit schedule.
RecurrenceSchedule.label: Recurrence Schedule

RedirectWhitelistUrl.description: Represents a trusted URL for external user redirections.
RedirectWhitelistUrl.label: Allow URL for Redirects

ReferenceDataLoadLog.description: Represents information about the history of loading reference data for emissions factors.
ReferenceDataLoadLog.label: Reference Data Load Log

Referral.description: Represents the information on client referrals in an organization.

RefrigerantEmssnFctr.description: Represents the global warming potential values for individual refrigerants. Global warming potential compares the atmospheric radiative forcing of one molecule of refrigerant to that of carbon dioxide.
RefrigerantEmssnFctr.label: Refrigerant Emissions Factor

Refund.description: Represents a refund made against a payment.
Refund.label: Refund

RefundLinePayment.description: A refund line that has been applied to a payment.
RefundLinePayment.label: Refund Line Payment

RegAuthorizationTypeProduct.description: Represents the association of authorization type and product.

RegisteredExternalService.description: Represents a registered external service used to provide an extension or integration.
RegisteredExternalService.label: Registered External Service

RegulatoryAuthority.description: Represents an organization or government agency that provides authorization. This object is available in API version 49.0 and later.

RegulatoryAuthorizationType.description: Represents the authorization issued by the regulatory body.

RegulatoryCode.description: Represents the regulation code enforced by the regulatory body.

RegulatoryCodeUse.description: Represents a junction between a set of assessment questions and the regulatory code associated with them.

RegulatoryCodeViolation.description: Represents the transactional violation data that has been identified during an inspection.

RegulatoryTrxnFee.description: Represents the association of regulatory transaction fees with your applications, inspections, or violations.

RegulatoryTrxnFeeItem.description: Represents the storage of specific fee items associated with your regulatory transaction fees.

RelatedListColumnDefinition.description: Represents information about a column in a related list. A related list specifies a set of records for a related object, based on specific criteria.
RelatedListColumnDefinition.label: Related List Column Definition

RelatedListDefinition.description: Represents information about a related list. A related list specifies a set of records for a related object, based on specific criteria.
RelatedListDefinition.label: Related List Definition

RelatedRecordAssocCriteria.description: Defines criteria for automatically linking records like accounts, leads, opportunities, and cases with the branches that work with them.
RelatedRecordAssocCriteria.label: Related Record Association Criteria

RelationshipGraphDefinition.description: Represents a definition of a graph that you can configure in your organization to traverse object hierarchies and record details, giving you a glimpse of how your business works.
RelationshipGraphDefinition.label: Relationship Graph Definition

RentalCarEmssnFctr.description: Represents the emissions factors for scope 3 rental car usage.
RentalCarEmssnFctr.label: Rental Car Emissions Factor

RentalCarEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to rental cars.
RentalCarEnrgyUse.label: Rental Car Energy Use

Reply.description: Represents a reply that a user has submitted to a question in an answers zone.

ReplyEmailSettings.description: Represents a reply mail management configuration, which is used to configure emails that are received by an email sending domain.
ReplyEmailSettings.label: Generic Reply Email Setting Result

ReplyReportAbuse.description: Represents a user-reported abuse on a Reply in a Chatter Answers zone.

ReplyText.description: A text reply generated by Einstein Reply Recommendations that is based on closed chat transcripts. Admins review replies and publish them to quick text, editing them as needed. Einstein recommends relevant published replies to support agents in the Lightning Service Console, and agents can insert replies into chats or messaging sessions.

Report Event Type.description: Report events contain information about what happened when a user ran a report. This event type includes all activity that's in the Report Export event type, plus more. For example, it has user activity for reports exported as both Formatted Report and Details Only output.

Report Export Event Type.description: Report Export events contain details about reports that a user exported. For example, this event type captures when a user exports a report as Details Only output. But it doesn’t capture reports that users export as Formatted Report or XLSX Detail output. For that data, see the Report event type.

ReportEventLog.description: Report event logs contain information about what happened when a user ran a report. This event type includes all activity that's in the Report Export event type, and additional information. For example, it has user activity for reports exported as both Formatted Report and Details Only output.

ReportExportEventLog.description: Report Export events contain details about reports that a user exported. For example, this event type captures when a user exports a report as Details Only output. But it doesn’t capture reports that users export as Formatted Report or XLSX Detail output. For that data, see the Report event type.

ReportTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Report.

ReputationLevelLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of a reputation level. Reputation level localization only applies for reputation levels in Experience Cloud sites.
ReputationLevelLocalization.label: Translation

ResidentialLoanApplication.description: Represents details about a loan application from the lender.
ResidentialLoanApplication.label: Residential Loan Application

ResourceAbsence.description: Fields associated with a time period in which a service resource is unavailable to work in Field Service.
ResourceAbsence.label: Resource Absence

ResourcePreference.description: Represents an account’s preference for a specified service resource on field service work.
ResourcePreference.label: Resource Preference

RestApiEventLog.description: REST API event logs contain details about REST-specific requests.

RetailLocationGroup.description: Group retail stores based on shared features, such as size, location, part of a retail chain.

RetailStore.description: Create records for physical retail stores associated to business accounts.

RetailStoreGroupAssignment.description: Represents a junction between a retail store and a retail store group.

RetailStoreKpi.description: Map store groups to assessment indicator definition, products, and in-store location categories and define targets. Targets are the expected compliance values for each assessment indicator definition, which is a parameter based on which markers of compliance are decided for a task.

RetailVisitKpi.description: Capture the actual information during a visit against the defined assessment indicator definition and target values.

RetrievalSummaryDefField.description: Represents a table that stores the fields to retrieve from the target object of a rollup definition.
RetrievalSummaryDefField.label: Retrieval Summary Definition Field

RetrievalSummaryDefObject.description: Represents a table that stores the rollup definitions of a retrieval definition.
RetrievalSummaryDefObject.label: Retrieval Summary Definition Object

RetrievalSummaryDefinition.description: Represents a table that stores the header information of a retrieval definition.
RetrievalSummaryDefinition.label: Retrieval Summary Definition

ReturnOrder.description: Represents the repair, return, or recall of product items.
ReturnOrder.label: Return Order

ReturnOrderItemAdjustment.description: Represents a price adjustment on a return order line item.
ReturnOrderItemAdjustment.label: Return Order Item Adjustment

ReturnOrderItemTax.description: Represents the tax on a return order line item or return order item adjustment.
ReturnOrderItemTax.label: Return Order Item Tax

ReturnOrderLineItem.description: Represents a product that is returned, recalled, or repaired as part of a return order.
ReturnOrderLineItem.label: Return Order Line Item

ReturnOrderOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a return order with user records other than the owner or anyone above the owner in the role hierarchy.
ReturnOrderOwnerSharingRule.label: Return Order Owner Rule

RevenueAsyncOperation.description: Represents the status of an asynchronous process initiated by a REST request in Subscription Management.
RevenueAsyncOperation.label: Revenue Async Operation

RevenueSourceCategoryConfig.description: Represents the Revenue Data Source-related stage information and the revenue metric that you want to measure and track.

RevenueSourceObjectConfig.description: Represents data from the underlying Salesforce standard or custom object that stores opportunity and product-related information.

RevenueTransactionErrorLog.description: Represents the details of errors that occurred during the processing of a request. The error record persists until a new error with the same category, primary record, and, if necessary, related record occurs.

RgltyCodeRegClauseVer.description: Represents a junction between Regulatory Code and Regulation Clause Version objects.

RgltyCodeViolRegClVer.description: Represents a junction between Regulatory Code Violation and Regulation Clause Version objects.

RuleTerritory2Association.description: Represents a record-assignment rule and its association to an object, such as Account. Available if Sales Territories has been enabled.
RuleTerritory2Association.label: Rule Territory Association

SOAP API Event Type.description: SOAP API events contain details about your org's SOAP API request activity.

SOQLResult.description: A complex type that represents the result of a SOQL query in an ApexExecutionOverlayResult object.

SOSDeployment.description: Represents the general settings for deploying SOS video call capability in a native mobile application.
SOSDeployment.label: SOS Deployment

SOSSession.description: This object is automatically created for each SOS session and stores information about the session.
SOSSession.label: SOS Session

SOSSessionActivity.description: Captures information about specific events that occur during an SOS video call, such as when an SOS call begins or ends.
SOSSessionActivity.label: SOS Session Activity

SalesAIScoreCycle.description: Represents the cycle type and ID used to score records.
SalesAIScoreCycle.label: Sales AI Score Cycle

SalesAIScoreModelFactor.description: Represents the factors that Sales Cloud Einstein uses to build a scoring model. Scoring models are used by features, such as Opportunity Scoring, to score individual records.
SalesAIScoreModelFactor.label: Sales AI Score Model Factor

SalesAgreeProductAttribute.description: Represents a virtual object that stores the key-value pairs for attributes of sales agreement products.

SalesAgreement.description: Represents a long-term agreement between a buyer and a seller to negotiate price and volume of products.

SalesAgreementProdSchdAdj.description: Represents the manual adjustments made to metric values for a sales agreement product schedule.

SalesAgreementProduct.description: Represents the total quantity or amount and the default pricing information of a product or category across the total time period of the sales agreement.

SalesAgreementProductSchedule.description: Represents the quantity or amount and the pricing information of a product or category for a particular schedule of the sales agreement.

SalesChannel.description: Represents the origin of an order. For example, a web storefront, physical store, marketplace, or mobile app. If you integrate Salesforce Order Management with Salesforce B2C Commerce, set up a SalesChannel corresponding to each Site in your B2C Commerce implementation.
SalesChannel.label: Sales Channel

SalesContractLine.description: Stores a contract's product information, including price, quantity, and components covered.
SalesContractLine.label: Sales Contract Line

SalesStoreCatalog.description: Represents the catalog associated with a store.
SalesStoreCatalog.label: Sales Store Catalog

SalesTransactionFulfillReq.description: Represents the statuses of all the sub-orders that belong to the selected commercial or technical product.

SalesTransactionItemShape.description: Defines the business logic for a sales transaction shape item, for example, an item in an order.

SalesTransactionShape.description: Defines the business logic for a sales transaction; for example, an order, a quote, or a cart.

SalesTransactionType.description: Represents the type of the sales transaction.

SalesTrxnItemRelationShape.description: Describes the relationship between sales transaction shape items; for example, a bundle or set.

SalesTrxnItemRelationship.description: Describes the relationship between sales transaction items; for example, a bundle or set.

SalesWorkQueueSettings.description: Represents settings used to customize work queue options for third-party scoring. Third-party scoring enables custom number fields on person accounts, contacts, and leads. You must be a Sales Engagement customer to update this object. Previously, you could only use the Einstein Intelligence Score for third-party scoring.

Salesforce Surveys Object Model.description: Learn about how Salesforce Surveys objects relate to one another in Salesforce.

SalesforceContract.description: Read-only virtual object used in the Your Account App.

SalesforceInvoice.description: Read-only virtual object used in the Your Account App. Represents information about your organization’s invoices with Salesforce.

SalesforceLoginAsEventLog.description: Salesforce LoginAs Event provides details about the Salesforce User's login into Customer Org as Customer's authorized user.

SalesforcePayment.description: Read-only virtual object used in the Your Account App. Represents information about payments related to your organization’s Salesforce invoice.

SalesforceQuote.description: Read-only virtual object used in the Your Account App. Represents information about your organization’s quotes with Salesforce.

Sandbox Event Type.description: Sandbox events contain details about sandbox copies.

SandboxProcess.description: Represents the sandbox copy process for a SandboxInfo record.
SandboxProcess.label: Sandbox Process

SandboxStatusEventLog.description: SandboxStatusEventLog stores details about Sandbox copies.

SavedPaymentMethod.description: Represents a payment method saved by an authenticated customer.

ScheduleBrdcstApptResource.description: Represents a junction between a Schedule Broadcast Appointment and a Service Resource. This object represents the resources to whom a schedule broadcast is sent.
ScheduleBrdcstApptResource.label: Schedule Broadcast Appointment Resource

ScheduleBroadcast.description: Represents a broadcast of appointments that's sent to resources of specific service territories.
ScheduleBroadcast.label: Schedule Broadcast

ScheduleBroadcastAppointment.description: Represents appointments that schedulers broadcast to resources using a schedule broadcast.
ScheduleBroadcastAppointment.label: Schedule Broadcast Appointment

ScheduleBroadcastTerritory.description: Represent service territories to which a schedule broadcast is sent.
ScheduleBroadcastTerritory.label: Schedule Broadcast Territory

SchedulingAdherenceDetail.description: Represents the breakdown of daily shift adherence data by agent status.

SchedulingAdherenceSummary.description: Represents daily shift adherence data for a service resource in a service territory and job profile on a specific date.

SchedulingConstraint.description: Represents scheduling constraints on each service resource.
SchedulingConstraint.label: Scheduling Constraint

SchedulingObjective.description: Represents scheduling objective settings for Workforce Engagement.
SchedulingObjective.label: Scheduling Objective

SchedulingRule.description: Represents scheduling rule settings for Workforce Engagement.
SchedulingRule.label: Scheduling Rule

SchedulingRuleParameter.description: Represents scheduling rule parameters associated with a scheduling rule.
SchedulingRuleParameter.label: Scheduling Rule Parameter

ScontrolLocalization.description: The translated value of the field label for an s-control.
ScontrolLocalization.label: Scontrol Localization

Scope3CrbnFtprnt.description: Represents the total carbon emissions from scope 3 activities. Carbon footprint quantifies the effect of atmospheric warming, which is represented in metric tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalent (tCO₂e).
Scope3CrbnFtprnt.label: Scope 3 Carbon Footprint

Scope3EmssnSrc.description: Represents scope 3 activities that are the source of greenhouse gas emissions.
Scope3EmssnSrc.label: Scope 3 Emissions Source

Scope3PcmtItem.description: Represents the procurement (corporate spending) entry records. Procurement is considered as the amount that the organization spends on goods and services.
Scope3PcmtItem.label: Scope 3 Procurement Item
